The paper presents new datasets for training face and object detection models in fisheye images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of a model for mapping regular to fisheye images, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The datasets can be used for training machine learning models, indicating the relevance of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category. The paper also mentions segmentation modules for fisheye images, which falls under the scope of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the datasets can be used for robotics applications, which suggests the relevance of cs.RO (Robotics and Control) as a possible sub-category.
